<paragraph id="8B846108FFB4F931FF5BF984FCF7FF70" blockId="38.[151,1436,294,2017]" lastBlockId="39.[151,1436,158,222]" lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="236" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">
Finally, I consider it useful to add that the examination of the many specimens preserved in the collections of MSNG, of the pair from 
<collectingCountry id="F32C2198FFB4F930FE7EF9B9FDDCF923" box="[481,582,1651,1677]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
kindly sent to me for study by Michel Secq, and of the specimens from Frasassi (CPV), showed that very few specimens possess, on the pigidium, the famous “ 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FB24F953FAFBF91C" box="[1211,1377,1689,1714]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">ligne médiane</emphasis>
[…] 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FF08F975FF51F976" box="[151,203,1727,1752]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">lisse</emphasis>
” described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFB4F930FEE0F975FD86F977" author="Auzat, V." box="[383,540,1727,1753]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="145 - 147" refId="ref72328" refString="Auzat, V. (1923) Description d'un nouveau Gnathoncus de Sardaigne (Coleopt. Hist.). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 55 (10), 145 - 147." type="journal article" year="1923">Auzat (1923)</bibRefCitation>
and which according to this author “ 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FC49F975FB66F976" box="[982,1276,1727,1752]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">distingue à première vue</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1A8BFFB4F930FA9AF975FA06F977" authorityName="Auzat" authorityYear="1923" box="[1285,1436,1727,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Gnathoncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerberus">Gn. cerberus</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FF08F92FFE73F950" box="[151,489,1765,1790]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">des autres espèces du genre</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1A8BFFB4F930FE6CF92FFD1CF951" box="[499,646,1765,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Gnathoncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Gnathoncus</taxonomicName>
”. This feature, highlighted by all subsequent authors (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFB4F930FAD8F92FFF4FF88A" author="Vienna, P." pageId="38" pageNumber="235" refId="ref76703" refString="Vienna, P. (1980) Fauna d'Italia XVI. Coleoptera Histeridae. Calderini, Bologna, 373 pp." type="book" year="1980">Vienna 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFB4F930FF7CF8C0FE74F88A" author="Thomas, H. &amp; Secq, M." box="[227,494,1802,1828]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="207 - 208" refId="ref76622" refString="Thomas, H. &amp; Secq, M. (2000) Gnathoncus cerberus Auzat, 1923: une espece nouvelle pour la faune Bulgare (Coleoptere Histeridae). Bulletin de la Societe Linneenne de Bordeaux, 28 (4), 207 - 208." type="journal article" year="2000">Thomas &amp; Secq 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFB4F930FE62F8C0FCA5F88A" author="Lackner, T. &amp; Pavicevic, D." box="[509,831,1802,1828]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="423 - 426" refId="ref74144" refString="Lackner, T. &amp; Pavicevic, D. (2008) Faunistic note on newly recorded and rare species of Histeridae from Serbia (Coleoptera). In: Pavicevic, D. &amp; Perreau, M. (Eds), Advances in the studies of the fauna of the Balkan Peninsula. Papers dedicated to the memory of Guido Nonveiller. Institute for Nature Conservation of Serbia, Belgrade, Monograph 22, pp. 423 - 426." type="journal article" year="2008">Lackner &amp; Pavićević 2008</bibRefCitation>
) and always used in the identification keys of the Palearctic species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1A8BFFB4F930FD8FF8FBFCE9F8E4" authority="Jacquelin du Val" authorityName="Jacquelin du Val" box="[528,883,1840,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Gnathoncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FD8FF8FBFD04F8E4" box="[528,670,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">Gnathoncus</emphasis>
Jacquelin du Val
</taxonomicName>
, is deceitful and often misleading considering that a smooth, median longitudinal band is sometimes more or less obvious in specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1A8BFFB4F930FB69F89CFE86F838" authority="(Kugelann)" baseAuthorityName="Kugelann" baseAuthorityYear="1792" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Gnathoncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundatus">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FB69F89CFA91F8C1" box="[1270,1291,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FA82F89CFA06F8C1" box="[1309,1436,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">rotundatus</emphasis>
(Kugelann)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1A8BFFB4F930FEFEF8B6FD0CF838" authority="(Marseul)" baseAuthorityName="Marseul" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[353,662,1916,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Gnathoncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nannetensis">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FEFEF8B6FEECF83B" box="[353,374,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FE14F8B6FD8FF83B" box="[395,533,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">nannetensis</emphasis>
(Marseul)
</taxonomicName>
(Penati pers. obs.; Secq 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FC4BF8B6FBDEF83B" box="[980,1092,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">in litteris</emphasis>
). On the contrary, the best character for distinguishing 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1A8BFFB4F930FE7EF868FDF0F815" authorityName="Auzat" authorityYear="1923" box="[481,618,1954,1980]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Gnathoncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerberus">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FE7EF868FE6CF815" box="[481,502,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFB4F930FD9BF868FDF0F815" box="[516,618,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">cerberus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other species with smooth intervals between the punctuation at the tip of the elytra is, in my opinion, the particular sculpture of the pygidium, characterized by transversely elongate punctures, set far apart and lying on an almost completely smooth surface; these punctures are instead more marked and more tightly set in the other species.
</paragraph>
